> Move over, Hawaiian pizza—there's a new pineapple-centric dinner in town. Here,
> we make an easy pineapple salsa with just fresh cilantro, lime juice, and onion
> for a delightfully sweet and savory condiment.

> It doesn't stop there, though—the juice is simmered with rich spices to create
> a tantalizingly sticky glaze for ground beef. It's all joined by fluffy rice,
> sautéed pepper and onion, smoky red pepper crema, and lime for brightness.
> One bite will have you totally BOWL-ed over.

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}; mince a few slices until you have
@onion{2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice;
roughly chop. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Halve,
core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips.

== Rice ==

In a small #pot{}, combine @white rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4
servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce
to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Pineapple Salsa ==

While rice cooks, in a small #bowl{}, combine minced onion, chopped pineapple,
half the cilantro, and a big squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

== Vegetables ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
sliced onion and green pepper; season with half the @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}
(you'll use the rest in the next step), salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until veggies are browned and softened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

> If seasoning begins to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium bowl and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

== Ground Beef ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz};
using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until browned
on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, remaining
@Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, and reserved pineapple juice. Bring to a simmer
and cook until sauce has thickened and beef is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}
more. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

> Open package of chicken and drain off any excess liquid. Swap in chicken (no
> need to break up into pieces!) or turkey for beef.

== Cilantro Lime Rice ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest, remaining cilantro, and
@butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with beef, veggies, and pineapple salsa.
Drizzle with @smoky red pepper crema{2%tbsp} and serve with remaining lime wedges
on the side.